Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.25,0:00:32.21,Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1528,188)\blur0.25\fs33\fnGeorgia\fsp3.0\c&HF8CC9E&\t(2529,5824,\c&HFAFBFA&)\pos(326,245)}Beyond Journey's End
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.98,0:01:32.98,Signs_EpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\c&HFAFFF7&\pos(384,269.5)}Episode 32: Other People's Homes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.75,0:01:50.02,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, which do you \Nthink would be better?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.61,0:01:53.15,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What difference does it make?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.15,0:01:56.21,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Also, can you do my hair \Nbefore you go out?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.62,0:02:04.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.96,0:02:09.33,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll apologize, okay? \NJust don't braid out of anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.86,0:02:35.37,Flashback,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,If you're that desperate for attention, \Nlet's go on a date tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.46,0:02:51.89,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.39,0:02:54.36,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.30,0:03:06.98,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You're not wearing your usual clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.98,0:03:07.80,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.30,0:03:12.66,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say this was a date?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.78,0:03:15.20,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.17,0:03:20.37,Default,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I was so surprised!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.37,0:03:21.42,Default,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.08,0:03:35.49,DefaultItalics,STARK/ID,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Has Fern always been this cute?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.71,0:03:38.88,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,A-Anyway, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.56,0:03:43.13,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Stark, your movements \Nseem quite forced today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.13,0:03:44.64,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,No, they're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.68,0:03:51.70,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.28,0:03:55.83,Default,FER,0000,0000,0000,,So, where are we going?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.23,0:03:59.22,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,There's a marketplace. \NLet's go check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.47,0:04:07.94,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Ms. Frieren \Nvisited it several times.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.73,0:04:15.23,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. She said sometimes markets in \Nbig cities have unusual magical items.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.48,0:04:19.65,Flashback,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Wow. Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.84,0:04:24.43,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why there was a mountain \Nof odd magical items at the inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.86,0:04:26.24,Flashback,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.58,0:04:29.23,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I can picture that disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.23,0:04:32.25,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,The other day, she even fell asleep \Nunder a pile of magical items.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.67,0:04:33.91,Flashback,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.91,0:04:36.26,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be kind of scary at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.26,0:04:37.25,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It was.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.94,0:04:41.87,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think Frieren is visiting \Nthe hot springs again today?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.40,0:04:45.90,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Surely she's tired of it by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.90,0:04:50.09,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. She's been going \Nevery day recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.83,0:04:54.68,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,And today, she didn't tie her hair up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.91,0:04:59.31,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,So good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.31,0:05:03.15,Default,OLD WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,You've gone with a cute \Nhairstyle today, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.29,0:05:10.64,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We always end up talking \Nabout Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.27,0:05:14.42,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like there's \Nanything else to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.83,0:05:22.18,Default,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look! I'll give you a discount!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.18,0:05:24.00,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to get something to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.43,0:05:26.42,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.00,0:05:28.24,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.39,0:05:42.19,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.07,0:05:46.06,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently couples get a discount.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.08,0:05:49.52,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Being on a date has its benefits.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.28,0:05:52.26,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You're rather blunt, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.50,0:05:59.67,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, all this stuff is pretty ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.67,0:06:03.05,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be surprised if they \Nwere all magical items.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.05,0:06:04.87,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You have a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.06,0:06:09.92,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Since we're in a city, let's check \Nout some other places, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.57,0:06:15.24,Default,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,This is cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.24,0:06:15.92,Default,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.39,0:06:18.18,Default,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could I get this, miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.18,0:06:19.21,Default,SHOPKEEPER,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.21,0:06:20.47,Default,SHOPKEEPER,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.18,0:06:22.79,DefaultTop,SHOPKEEPER,0000,0000,0000,,You're a couple of lovebirds, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.23,0:06:24.43,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You must be hungry by now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.43,0:06:27.09,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,There were some stalls selling \Ntasty-looking food over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.07,0:06:31.86,Default,SHOPKEEPER,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.86,0:06:34.17,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,These look so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.17,0:06:35.88,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,There are tables over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.88,0:06:36.57,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.54,0:06:43.90,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.33,0:06:46.43,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.07,0:06:50.43,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.27,0:06:55.92,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It does seem hard to walk in those shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.87,0:07:38.50,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,There are statues of \NMr. Himmel in every city.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.50,0:07:41.41,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,His pose in this city \Nwas pretty handsome, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.83,0:07:43.05,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It was.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.31,0:07:47.97,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,According to Frieren, there are \Nover a hundred different poses.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.39,0:07:50.52,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,They made a few too many, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.52,0:07:51.51,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.65,0:07:58.87,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We ended up talking about \NMs. Frieren again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.03,0:08:06.30,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, this is a nice, quiet place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.02,0:08:08.66,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,The view is pretty, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.13,0:08:10.46,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.37,0:08:18.97,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Fern, did you not have fun today?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.92,0:08:22.72,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.28,0:08:25.81,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't smiled once.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.66,0:08:34.62,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Well... I did like all \Nthe places we visited,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.05,0:08:36.12,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,but for some reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.96,0:08:40.21,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,it didn't feel like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.34,0:08:44.87,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I was looking forward to our date, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.87,0:08:48.24,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.49,0:08:53.51,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I actually had Frieren \Nchoose those places.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.00,0:08:57.00,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.41,0:09:01.63,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Because I really wanted you to enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.44,0:09:05.30,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,We've never been on a date before, \Nso I wanted it to be special.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.01,0:09:09.32,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.66,0:09:15.97,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,True, I was slightly disappointed \Nby today, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.52,0:09:19.19,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.89,0:09:23.79,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You really racked your brain for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.95,0:09:26.03,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Fern...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.20,0:09:33.56,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,This is such a peaceful, quiet moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.11,0:09:37.79,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that cloud look familiar?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.20,0:09:41.10,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's one of the pork buns we ate earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.55,0:09:43.45,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I was thinking the same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.54,0:09:52.11,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.79,0:09:58.10,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,When I was a war orphan, I never \Nthought I'd get to relax like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.66,0:10:00.07,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.84,0:10:03.08,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I have Mr. Heiter to thank for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.58,0:10:06.08,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,And I have my master to thank.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.12,0:10:21.11,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,You won't become a strong \Nwarrior if you're picky.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.73,0:10:33.02,Flashback,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.61,0:10:34.65,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.33,0:10:38.14,Flashback,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you take me in?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.48,0:10:42.53,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's what Himmel \Nthe Hero would've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.18,0:10:55.65,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be in a good mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.13,0:10:57.67,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Did something good happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.52,0:11:00.61,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.97,0:11:07.93,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,So it wasn't here either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.44,0:11:09.63,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I'm stumped.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.14,0:11:14.03,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,We searched everywhere \Nthe shopkeeper could think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.53,0:11:18.57,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Himmel, why are you smiling?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.38,0:11:26.32,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in a good mood \Nbecause today was a good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.58,0:11:30.70,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,All we did was walk around \Nlooking for a lost cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.07,0:11:36.46,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but I had fun going out with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.14,0:11:39.34,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we never found the cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.09,0:11:45.18,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Even if things don't go as you'd hoped, \Nyou can still enjoy the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.66,0:11:49.85,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,That alone is enough to put \Nsomeone in a good mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.25,0:11:51.41,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.67,0:11:53.48,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.17,0:11:58.70,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Let's give it another shot before \NHeiter and Eisen beat us to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.27,0:12:04.60,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,There it is, Himmel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.95,0:12:07.06,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,That must be it. Let's catch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.63,0:12:18.87,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Your hair's braided again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.40,0:12:23.02,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,These are the braids I get \Nwhen Fern's in a good mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.52,0:12:25.13,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I can't tell the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.43,0:12:28.13,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Don't I look good?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.13,0:12:31.01,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I really can't tell the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.97,0:12:35.98,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\pos(588,147)}29 years after the death\Nof Himmel the Hero,\Nin the Nachricht region,\Nlocated in the northern lands
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.97,0:12:38.74,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It's gotten cold again lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.74,0:12:40.99,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We're out of the volcanic area now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.94,0:12:43.99,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We should be able to see it soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.33,0:12:48.91,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Is that the Northern Plateau checkpoint?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.23,0:12:51.56,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It's so imposing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.56,0:12:54.26,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Because what's beyond it \Nis just that dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.25,0:13:05.37,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We probably won't have decent \Naccess to supplies for a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.37,0:13:07.71,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,so let's get everything we need.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.70,0:13:23.08,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That suitcase fits more \Nthan it looks like it would.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.08,0:13:24.77,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Convenient, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.34,0:13:43.01,Default,GUARD,0000,0000,0000,,So you're Fern, a first-class mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.35,0:13:44.59,Default,GUARD,0000,0000,0000,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.88,0:13:51.89,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I guess Fern's pretty impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.89,0:13:56.26,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,First-class mages are \Nthe greatest of all mages.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.80,0:14:04.42,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the Northern Plateau.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.02,0:14:10.03,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It seems pretty normal, considering \Nhow dangerous everyone said it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.00,0:14:13.97,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you being serious, Mr. Stark?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.59,0:14:15.71,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.51,0:14:20.04,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We're surrounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.92,0:14:25.49,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Look sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.59,0:14:28.62,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This is just the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.85,0:15:19.34,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a village.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.84,0:15:23.08,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I was going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.78,0:15:26.60,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We did have to stay alert \Nfor three days and nights.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.30,0:15:29.18,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I hope we can rest here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.24,0:15:32.57,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.08,0:15:34.95,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,There's a cabin nobody's using.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.39,0:15:36.99,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,Feel free to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.65,0:15:38.78,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.81,0:15:43.21,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to ask, but in exchange...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.29,0:15:50.67,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,A powerful monster started frequenting \Nthe main road past here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.04,0:15:56.42,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,The local knights are \Npowerless against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.25,0:16:00.42,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,Traveling merchants can \Nno longer pass this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.24,0:16:04.44,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, \Nadventurers rarely visit this land.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.94,0:16:08.70,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,Would you please slay \Nthat monster for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.92,0:16:11.89,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. We're going north anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.89,0:16:13.69,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll slay it on our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.82,0:16:16.44,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're okay with that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.44,0:16:17.33,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.59,0:16:21.04,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.82,0:16:24.87,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,But it's just a three-day trip south
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.87,0:16:27.72,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,along the main road \Nto leave the Northern Plateau.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.78,0:16:32.21,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need for you to live \Nin this dangerous place, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.50,0:16:38.64,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,This area is certainly dangerous, \Neven by the northern lands' standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.28,0:16:43.85,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,But we were born and raised here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.46,0:16:51.71,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,The land is full of our \Nmemories of our families.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.12,0:16:55.70,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,Who could abandon their home?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.96,0:17:03.69,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.93,0:17:09.34,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,We're counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.70,0:17:57.75,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This must be the monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.09,0:17:59.76,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let your guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.48,0:18:13.48,DefaultItalics,FERN/ID,0000,0000,0000,,I can't get a clear shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.16,0:18:25.28,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It's different from the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.78,0:18:28.07,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This seems like a formidable foe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.46,0:18:45.39,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The methods we've been using \Nwon't work against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.19,0:18:47.61,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It certainly seems that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.16,0:18:49.00,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.65,0:19:18.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it noticed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.28,0:19:25.43,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Stark, lock it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.43,0:19:26.66,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.97,0:19:41.61,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It's tough, but so am I!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.94,0:19:43.88,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let it beat me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.88,0:19:45.50,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.27,0:20:14.49,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That thing was pretty strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.28,0:20:18.38,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We've still only just entered \Nthe Northern Plateau.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.38,0:20:23.29,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Going forward, we'll face \Nloads of monsters that strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.50,0:20:26.90,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You mean things like that \Nare all over the place?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.36,0:20:28.69,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,That will be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.26,0:20:30.40,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.96,0:20:35.13,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we should've traveled \Nby sea after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.10,0:20:38.66,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I think it'd be worth the price.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.63,0:20:48.55,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't expecting to find \Nsuch a powerful monster here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.98,0:20:51.28,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I was going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.95,0:20:56.01,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,If it's going to be this dangerous, we \Nshould have sailed around the whole area.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.49,0:20:58.07,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we came this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.75,0:21:03.15,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Many people live on the Northern Plateau.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.15,0:21:09.30,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I became a hero because \NI wanted to protect my homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.21,0:21:13.10,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,So I want to protect \Nother people's homes, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.66,0:21:20.49,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Stark, many people call \Nthe Northern Plateau home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.96,0:21:37.74,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.91,0:21:40.54,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do our best.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.54,0:21:43.24,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fire yourselves up for the road ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.24,0:21:44.09,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.45,0:21:49.48,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We made it through that fight \Nthanks to Stark's last-ditch effort,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.48,0:21:53.66,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,but we'll have to focus more \Non teamwork going forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.23,0:21:55.41,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.38,0:22:00.66,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Stark, \Nwhy are you still sitting?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.11,0:22:04.92,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sitting.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.87,0:22:09.58,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,My legs gave out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.38,0:22:13.01,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.01,0:22:14.92,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I can't help it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.92,0:22:19.63,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that crazy spell \Nwas going to kill me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.90,0:22:25.03,Credits,CREDITS,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(526,517)\fs10\pos(525,120)}Translation\N{\fs12}Sho Stifler\N\N{\fs10}Editing & Typesetting\N{\fs12}Geoff Mazzolini\N\N{\fs10}Subtitle Timing\N{\fs12}Edgar Cruz\N\N{\fs10}Quality Check\N{\fs12}Alicia Ashby\N\N{\fs10}Translation Check\N{\fs12}Elizabeth Ellis
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.02,0:23:52.43,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't come crying to me later.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.84,0:23:52.88,DefaultOverlap,MILLIARDE,0000,0000,0000,,So that they don't end up like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.67,0:23:53.44,DefaultTop,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, what am I going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.41,0:23:55.38,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,All we can do is buy back Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.20,0:23:54.99,DefaultOverlap,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.88,0:23:56.63,DefaultTop,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,I did it for that legendary liquor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.99,0:23:57.49,DefaultOverlap,MINER,0000,0000,0000,,The president told us about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.60,0:23:58.07,Default,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.53,0:23:59.99,Signs_NextEp,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(229,1)\blur3\t(20,312,\blur0.2)\pos(320,113.5)\c&H000000&\t(312,646,\c&HF6F6F6&)\fsp1.6\t(\fsp1)}Episode 33\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NLogistics in the Northern Plateau
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.07,0:24:00.03,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,Logistics in the Northern Plateau.